==English==

===Verb phrase===
'''to [[pull]] oneself [[up]] [[by]] one's [[bootstraps]]'''

# {{idiom}} To begin an [[enterprise]] or recover from a [[setback]] without any [[outside]] [[help]]; to [[succeed]] only on one's own [[effort]] or [[abilities]].
#: ''We can't get a loan, so we'll just have to '''pull ourselves up by our bootstraps'''.''

